crash: possible deadlock in l2tp_tunnel_register
========================================================
WARNING: possible irq lock inversion dependency detected
6.1.0-rc4-syzkaller #0 Not tainted
--------------------------------------------------------
syz-executor.0/7516 just changed the state of lock:
ffff8880161803b8 (k-clock-AF_INET){+++.}-{2:2}, at: l2tp_tunnel_register+0x126/0x1210 mnt/sdd/author/SyzInspector/wd-bisector-7/kernel/net/l2tp/l2tp_core.c:1477
but this lock was taken by another, SOFTIRQ-safe lock in the past:
 (k-slock-AF_INET){+.-.}-{2:2}


and interrupts could create inverse lock ordering between them.


other info that might help us debug this:
 Possible interrupt unsafe locking scenario:

       CPU0                    CPU1
       ----                    ----
  lock(k-clock-AF_INET);
                               local_irq_disable();
                               lock(k-slock-AF_INET);
                               lock(k-clock-AF_INET);
  <Interrupt>
    lock(k-slock-AF_INET);

 *** DEADLOCK ***

